id: pm-psc0
title: Normalize stale audit containers and intentional-open resolved items
description: "Tracker cleanup for stale open audit containers and resolved-but-open items that should be closed, repurposed, or explicitly kept recurring without mis-bucketing release changelogs."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: audit,dedupe,normalization,pm-cli,tracker-governance
created_at: "2026-06-25T04:57:09.508Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-25T16:58:21.197Z"
author: codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: Stale audit containers and intentional-open resolved items are normalized in a dedicated tracker-only change or documented as deliberate open coordination containers; release-bearing changelog mis-bucketing is avoided; status-all duplicate evidence and current disposition comments are recorded before any closures.
parent: pm-doxj
resolution: Closed stale audit/session wrappers in a dedicated tracker-only pass and preserved living/recurring items with explicit rationale.
expected_result: Stale audit containers and intentional-open resolved items are normalized without duplicate tracker work or unexplained open wrappers.
actual_result: Six stale wrappers were closed and linked to pm-psc0; intentional living/recurring items remain open with rationale; verification gates and manual sandbox smoke passed.
