comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T04:57:09.508Z",codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625,"Duplicate check: status-all searches for stale open audit stories close normalization and tracker taxonomy hierarchy duplicate hygiene found active read-only lane pm-klpw plus closed prior audits, but no active cleanup execution item."
  "2026-06-25T05:15:09.780Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Evidence: closed stale audit wrappers pm-5dbn, pm-srex, pm-b4cp, pm-34gb, pm-lzrq, and pm-gpea after confirming no active descendants remained and current findings are closed or represented by current backlog. Kept pm-z5nb open as an intentional coordination container, pm-28cf open because its own notes require a non-release-bearing close to avoid changelog mis-bucketing, pm-7zs0 open as recurring release-health, and pm-96wm open as a living ADR."
  "2026-06-25T05:20:58.757Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Audit correction: stale-container closures were inspected but pruned from this product-fix PR to avoid changing old closed/open audit records and reclassifying unrelated historical work in CHANGELOG.md. Current intentional follow-up stays open here: pm-5dbn, pm-srex, pm-b4cp, pm-34gb, pm-lzrq, and pm-gpea need a dedicated tracker-only disposition pass; pm-z5nb, pm-28cf, pm-7zs0, and pm-96wm need explicit recurring/living rationale before closure decisions."
  "2026-06-25T16:51:55.416Z",codex,"Disposition evidence: status-all duplicate searches and current child checks found pm-5dbn, pm-srex, pm-b4cp, pm-34gb, pm-lzrq, and pm-gpea are stale audit/session containers with zero open descendants; their findings are either closed children or represented by current roadmap items. Keeping intentional-open items unchanged: pm-z5nb is an explicit coordination container kept out of release changelogs; pm-28cf is already satisfied by #254 and requires only a dedicated non-release-bearing closure later; pm-7zs0 is a recurring release-health reminder and remains claimed by the prior release-health lane; pm-96wm remains a living ADR under the ADR epic."
  "2026-06-25T16:58:07.699Z",codex,"Evidence: normalized six stale audit/session wrappers (pm-5dbn, pm-srex, pm-b4cp, pm-34gb, pm-lzrq, pm-gpea) to closed after descendant checks showed zero open child work; linked them as related dependencies from pm-psc0. Kept living/recurring items open with rationale recorded. Verification passed: pnpm build; static-quality gate ok with source docstrings 237/237 and exported docstrings 1840/1840; pm validate ok with known pre-existing resolution warnings and history_drift ok; pm health summary ok; pnpm audit moderate clean; pnpm changelog:pm regenerated CHANGELOG.md and pnpm changelog:pm:check passed; full coverage passed 100/100/100/100 (254 files, 5104 tests); manual temp smoke passed in /tmp/pm-cli-manual-smoke-c6u88v using sandboxed PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH."
